[
    {
        "text": "Hello, and welcome to engVid.",
        "start": 0.299,
        "duration": 2.731
    },
    {
        "text": "My name's Benjamin.",
        "start": 3.03,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "This is a lesson for Chinese speakers of English.",
        "start": 4.38,
        "duration": 5.3
    },
    {
        "text": "One-fifth of the world's population speak\nChinese.",
        "start": 9.68,
        "duration": 4.87
    },
    {
        "text": "The world will become a smaller place if we\ncan communicate and we have something that",
        "start": 14.55,
        "duration": 5.76
    },
    {
        "text": "we can share - language.",
        "start": 20.31,
        "duration": 2.269
    },
    {
        "text": "So, I know it is a huge task if you are a\nChinese speaker and you're learning English;",
        "start": 22.579,
        "duration": 8.6
    },
    {
        "text": "the same for English people learning Chinese.",
        "start": 31.179,
        "duration": 1.801
    },
    {
        "text": "They are two very different languages, and\nI cannot in a 7-minute video teach you everything",
        "start": 32.98,
        "duration": 6.199
    },
    {
        "text": "you need to know, but in this video there\nare tips, there are pointers that should be",
        "start": 39.179,
        "duration": 7.761
    },
    {
        "text": "helpful to you in your study of English.",
        "start": 46.94,
        "duration": 4.34
    },
    {
        "text": "First, a pronunciation tip.",
        "start": 51.28,
        "duration": 5.219
    },
    {
        "text": "Consonant clusters can be difficult for Chinese\nspeakers.",
        "start": 56.499,
        "duration": 4.36
    },
    {
        "text": "What I mean here is where we have two consonants\ntogether.",
        "start": 60.859,
        "duration": 5.111
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 65.97,
        "duration": 1.33
    },
    {
        "text": "This is difficult, so I'm going to repeat\nthese words for you.",
        "start": 67.3,
        "duration": 5.47
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm going to say them, and hopefully you can\nsay them back at home as you are watching",
        "start": 72.77,
        "duration": 6.13
    },
    {
        "text": "this just to get used to these sounds.",
        "start": 78.9,
        "duration": 3.37
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 82.27,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "So, repeat after me: \"break\", \"break\".",
        "start": 83.27,
        "duration": 4.91
    },
    {
        "text": "The \"b\" goes with the \"r\".",
        "start": 88.18,
        "duration": 6.07
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Crave\", \"gloat\", \"spurn\".",
        "start": 94.25,
        "duration": 10.49
    },
    {
        "text": "It doesn't matter if you don't know the meanings\nof these words; I'm just getting you used",
        "start": 104.74,
        "duration": 4.91
    },
    {
        "text": "to saying them.",
        "start": 109.65,
        "duration": 3.29
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 112.94,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Flurry\", \"cradle\", \"grim\", \"grow\", \"crawl\".",
        "start": 115.31,
        "duration": 11.84
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, make sure you are saying these at home\njust to practice and get used to English sounds.",
        "start": 127.15,
        "duration": 7.31
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's go with the consonant cluster at the\nend: \"ble\", \"strel\", \"ble\", \"nate\", \"stic\".",
        "start": 134.46,
        "duration": 7.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 142.41,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Got two consonant sounds together.",
        "start": 143.41,
        "duration": 3.91
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Pliable\", \"minstrel\", \"incredible\", \"fortunate\",\n\"fantastic\".",
        "start": 147.32,
        "duration": 13.45
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.",
        "start": 160.77,
        "duration": 2.69
    },
    {
        "text": "Now we're going to look at ways of asking\nquestions.",
        "start": 163.46,
        "duration": 3.19
    },
    {
        "text": "There are so many different ways that you\ncan ask questions in English.",
        "start": 166.65,
        "duration": 3.72
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm going to take you through the main question\nwords.",
        "start": 170.37,
        "duration": 4.04
    },
    {
        "text": "So, we always start with the question word\nat the beginning of the sentence and that",
        "start": 174.41,
        "duration": 6.99
    },
    {
        "text": "shows what type of question it is.",
        "start": 181.4,
        "duration": 3.07
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 184.47,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "For example: \"Why\" looks at a reason, \"When\"\nlooks at a time, \"How\" looks at the method",
        "start": 185.47,
        "duration": 8.63
    },
    {
        "text": "in which something is done, \"Where\" is about\na place, \"Who\" is about a person, \"What\" is",
        "start": 194.1,
        "duration": 8.02
    },
    {
        "text": "about an object, \"Is\"... now, we use \"Is\"\nto ask... it tends to lend itself to a yes",
        "start": 202.12,
        "duration": 12.85
    },
    {
        "text": "or no question.",
        "start": 214.97,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Are\", so this is a version of the verb \"to\nbe\", so it's finding out someone... how someone",
        "start": 218.49,
        "duration": 9.7
    },
    {
        "text": "is.",
        "start": 228.19,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Are they good?",
        "start": 229.19,
        "duration": 1.11
    },
    {
        "text": "Are they happy?\"",
        "start": 230.3,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "etc.",
        "start": 231.44,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's go through some example questions.",
        "start": 232.44,
        "duration": 3.71
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Why are you learning English?",
        "start": 236.15,
        "duration": 5.03
    },
    {
        "text": "Why are you learning\", so subject, verb, object.",
        "start": 241.18,
        "duration": 6.88
    },
    {
        "text": "We want to know the reason.",
        "start": 248.06,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "\"When did you start?\"",
        "start": 250.31,
        "duration": 3.62
    },
    {
        "text": "Subject, verb.",
        "start": 253.93,
        "duration": 3.19
    },
    {
        "text": "\"When did you\", so past tense.",
        "start": 257.12,
        "duration": 3.53
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"When did you start?\"",
        "start": 260.65,
        "duration": 1.449
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"I started learning English two years ago.\"",
        "start": 262.099,
        "duration": 3.781
    },
    {
        "text": "\"How do you learn?",
        "start": 265.88,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "How\", so do you learn by reading?",
        "start": 268.86,
        "duration": 3.769
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you learn by writing?",
        "start": 272.629,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "By watching lessons on engVid?",
        "start": 273.919,
        "duration": 3.161
    },
    {
        "text": "Subject, verb.",
        "start": 277.08,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Where do you live?\"",
        "start": 280.24,
        "duration": 4.239
    },
    {
        "text": "Question word: \"Where do\".",
        "start": 284.479,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "So: \"Why are\", \"Where did\", \"When do\", \"Where\ndo\", \"Who is\", \"What is\".",
        "start": 286.249,
        "duration": 6.04
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 292.289,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "So, this is how we phrase one of these questions.",
        "start": 293.289,
        "duration": 3.22
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"Where do you live?\"",
        "start": 296.509,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"I live in China.",
        "start": 299.009,
        "duration": 2.451
    },
    {
        "text": "I live in Shanghai.\"",
        "start": 301.46,
        "duration": 1.229
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"Who is your favourite teacher?\"",
        "start": 302.689,
        "duration": 3.501
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"My favourite teacher is...\"",
        "start": 306.19,
        "duration": 2.619
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Benjamin\" is the answer, by the way.",
        "start": 308.809,
        "duration": 3.63
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"What is your favourite football team?\"",
        "start": 312.439,
        "duration": 3.34
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"My favourite football team is...\"",
        "start": 315.779,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"Is it hot where you are?\"",
        "start": 319.759,
        "duration": 3.541
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"No, it's not hot where I am; it's cold.\"",
        "start": 323.3,
        "duration": 3.7
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"Are you okay?\"",
        "start": 327.0,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "-\"Yes, thank you.",
        "start": 329.13,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm fine.\"",
        "start": 330.49,
        "duration": 5.019
    },
    {
        "text": "Joining words together in speech.",
        "start": 335.509,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "If we pronounce each word as a separate entity,\nthen it will sound very chopped up and it",
        "start": 338.789,
        "duration": 7.991
    },
    {
        "text": "needs more of a flow when we are speaking\nEnglish conversationally.",
        "start": 346.78,
        "duration": 6.169
    },
    {
        "text": "I'll demonstrate it not joined up: \"Later\non I'm going to meet up with my friends.",
        "start": 352.949,
        "duration": 9.0
    },
    {
        "text": "I expect I'll have some food and drinks.\"",
        "start": 361.949,
        "duration": 6.661
    },
    {
        "text": "But we join things when we're speaking English.",
        "start": 368.61,
        "duration": 4.959
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Later\", and then because we have a vowel\nhere, this consonant goes into the next sound:",
        "start": 373.569,
        "duration": 8.41
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Later on I'm going...",
        "start": 381.979,
        "duration": 3.321
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm going to meet\".",
        "start": 385.3,
        "duration": 2.329
    },
    {
        "text": "Again, the consonant goes into that vowel\nsound: \"I'm going to meet up, meet up, meet",
        "start": 387.629,
        "duration": 6.41
    },
    {
        "text": "up with my friends.",
        "start": 394.039,
        "duration": 2.69
    },
    {
        "text": "I expect\"... so, two vowels, you can also\njoin them: \"I expect I'll have, I'll have",
        "start": 396.729,
        "duration": 6.69
    },
    {
        "text": "some food and drinks.\"",
        "start": 403.419,
        "duration": 2.661
    },
    {
        "text": "And, again, that consonant goes into the vowel:\n\"food and drinks\".",
        "start": 406.08,
        "duration": 6.47
    },
    {
        "text": "General tips.",
        "start": 412.55,
        "duration": 2.229
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, tenses can be an area of difficulty for\nChinese learners.",
        "start": 414.779,
        "duration": 5.371
    },
    {
        "text": "There's lots of different videos on this site,\nlooking at the past tense, the present tense,",
        "start": 420.15,
        "duration": 4.519
    },
    {
        "text": "the future tense, conditionals, etc. so I\nwould suggest that you really get involved",
        "start": 424.669,
        "duration": 5.261
    },
    {
        "text": "and find... watch however many you can.",
        "start": 429.93,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "It will help.",
        "start": 432.55,
        "duration": 2.359
    },
    {
        "text": "Get familiar with intonation patterns.",
        "start": 434.909,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "How do you do that?",
        "start": 438.03,
        "duration": 1.059
    },
    {
        "text": "By listening to native English speakers.",
        "start": 439.089,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "How do our voices go up and down?",
        "start": 442.61,
        "duration": 3.309
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 445.919,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Spelling.",
        "start": 447.599,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm afraid this is something you're just going\nto have to remember, learn, practice.",
        "start": 449.289,
        "duration": 6.36
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 455.649,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "Practice, practice, practice.",
        "start": 457.069,
        "duration": 4.291
    },
    {
        "text": "Look at a word, try to remember how it's spelt,\ncover it up, write it down.",
        "start": 461.36,
        "duration": 6.259
    },
    {
        "text": "Did you get it right?",
        "start": 467.619,
        "duration": 1.061
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes or no?",
        "start": 468.68,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "If not, how's it spelt?",
        "start": 469.68,
        "duration": 1.269
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, go again and again and again.",
        "start": 470.949,
        "duration": 3.201
    },
    {
        "text": "Get familiar with the spread-out language.",
        "start": 474.15,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "I know your writing is much more condensed;\nyou're going to have to get used to writing",
        "start": 476.61,
        "duration": 4.209
    },
    {
        "text": "being... taking up more space than the Chinese\nscript.",
        "start": 480.819,
        "duration": 6.43
    },
    {
        "text": "And practice reading.",
        "start": 487.249,
        "duration": 1.801
    },
    {
        "text": "Fantastic.",
        "start": 489.05,
        "duration": 1.07
    },
    {
        "text": "You don't need me to tell you that there's\namazing books out there.",
        "start": 490.12,
        "duration": 3.539
    },
    {
        "text": "Pick one up that is for your ability; get\nreading; write down some good, new words;",
        "start": 493.659,
        "duration": 7.12
    },
    {
        "text": "and you'll enjoy it.",
        "start": 500.779,
        "duration": 1.01
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 501.789,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Talk to your friends about it.",
        "start": 502.789,
        "duration": 1.861
    },
    {
        "text": "Why not have a go at doing today's quiz?",
        "start": 504.65,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Stay in touch with me by pressing \"Subscribe\"\nso you watch my next lessons for you.",
        "start": 507.53,
        "duration": 5.41
    },
    {
        "text": "And I hope to see you back here again very\nsoon.",
        "start": 512.94,
        "duration": 2.889
    },
    {
        "text": "Take care.",
        "start": 515.829,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Goodbye.",
        "start": 516.829,
        "duration": 0.001
    }
]